## REPOSITORY STRUCTURE

All files must be created at their exact paths. Use the create_file tool directly — parent directories are created automatically.

```
grokking-reproduction/
├── .cursorrules             ← this file (already exists)
├── .gitignore
├── requirements.txt
├── PROJECT_MEMORY.md
├── PROJECT_EXPLAIN.md
├── abstract_draft.md
├── src/
│   ├── data.py
│   ├── model.py
│   ├── train.py
│   ├── analysis.py
│   ├── figures.py
│   └── utils.py
├── notebooks/
│   └── run_all.ipynb
├── outputs/                 ← created at runtime, not committed
└── checkpoints/             ← created at runtime, not committed
```

When producing any file, always state before the code block:
```
FILE: src/model.py
CHANGES: [one-line summary of what changed vs previous version]
DEPENDS ON: [list of files this imports from]
DEPENDED ON BY: [list of files that import this]
```

