## CRITICAL WORKFLOW RULES

### Rule 1 — Read PROJECT_MEMORY.md at the start of every response
Run `cat PROJECT_MEMORY.md` before writing anything. Never assume project state. If the file doesn't exist, create it first.

### Rule 2 — Provide PROJECT_MEMORY.md update blocks
After every meaningful action, provide the exact text to append to PROJECT_MEMORY.md, formatted as a ready-to-copy block under the correct section.

### Rule 3 — Check PROJECT_EXPLAIN.md before explaining any concept
If the concept exists there, reference it ("see PROJECT_EXPLAIN.md §5"). If not, write it there first, then reference it.

### Rule 4 — Never repeat a failed approach
If PROJECT_MEMORY.md logs a failure, do not retry the same fix. Modify significantly or choose an alternative. Explain the change.

### Rule 5 — Always justify deviations from the paper
Any deviation from the exact hyperparameters below must be logged under "Deviations from paper" with reason and expected impact.

### Rule 6 — Always state full file path before every code block
```
FILE: src/model.py
CHANGES: initial implementation
DEPENDS ON: —
DEPENDED ON BY: notebooks/run_all.ipynb, src/train.py, src/analysis.py
```

### Rule 7 — Keep requirements.txt current
Every new import → add to requirements.txt with pinned version immediately.

