## THE PAPER: WHAT TO REPRODUCE

**Citation:**
Nanda, N., Chan, L., Lieberum, T., Smith, J., & Steinhardt, J. (2023).
Progress Measures for Grokking via Mechanistic Interpretability.
ICLR 2023 (Oral). DOI: 10.48550/arXiv.2301.05217

**Minimum reproduction targets:**
1. Grokking curve: train/test accuracy diverge, then test catches up — final test acc ≥ 95%
2. Fourier structure in W_E: only ~3–5 frequencies dominate the power spectrum
3. Three progress measures precede the accuracy jump
4. Qualitative match with paper Figures 1, 3, 4, 5

---

## EXACT HYPERPARAMETERS (from paper — any deviation must be logged)

```
Task:            (a + b) mod p
p:               113  →  vocab_size = 114 (tokens 0..112 plus "=")
Input:           [a, b, =]  →  predict at position index 3
d_model:         128
num_heads:       4
d_mlp:           512  (= 4 × d_model)
num_layers:      1
activation:      ReLU
layer_norm:      pre-LN (applied before attention and MLP sublayers)
pos_embedding:   learned
optimizer:       AdamW
lr:              1e-3
weight_decay:    1.0
beta1:           0.9
beta2:           0.98
batch_size:      full dataset (all p² = 12769 pairs per step)
train_fraction:  0.3  (30% of pairs for train, 70% held out as test)
total_epochs:    20000
loss:            cross-entropy on last position logit only
seed:            42
```

